<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 7:37AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FOG ACROSS THE NORTHERN RANCHLANDS THIS MORNING...
Surface observations and satellite imagery indicate that patchy
fog has developed across northern Hidalgo, Jim Hogg, Brooks, and
inland Kenedy counties this morning. Reported visibilities
are generally in the range of 1 to 3 miles, though reports from
Falfurrias have been as low as 1/2 mile.
Motorists should use caution this morning, especially along U. S.
Highway 281 near Falfurrias. Use low beam headlights and leave
extra distance between your vehicle and others on the road.</description>
